INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 135","Photomedicine","4","Studies the use of optical and engineering-based systems (laser-based) for diagnosis, treating diseases, manipulation of cells and cell function. Physical, optical, and electro-optical principles are explored regarding molecular, cellular, organ, and organism applications."," PHYS 3C or PHYS 7D"," Biomedical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 136","Engineering Medical Optics","4","Principles of optics and photonics, integration of optical components into systems and devices, and analysis of physiological signals obtained from Biophotonics measurements."," BME 130 and (BME 135 or BIOL D130)"," Biomedical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 137","Introduction to Biomedical Imaging","4","Introduction to imaging modalities widely used in medicine and biology, including X-ray, computed tomography (CT), nuclear medicine (PET and SPET), ultrasonic imaging, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), optical tomography, imaging contrast, imaging processing, and complementary nature of the imaging modalities."," BME 130 or EECS 50 or EECS 150"," Biomedical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
