INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 212","Cardiovascular Mechanobiology","4","Advanced topics in cellular engineering and mechanobiology, with focus on the cardiovascular system.  Tools and techniques used to manipulate and measure mechanical forces at the molecular, cellular, tissue, and organ levels, and their applications in cardiovascular devices and tissue engineering.",""," Graduate students only.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 212P","Cardiovascular Mechanobiology","4","Advanced topics in cellular engineering and mechanobiology, with focus on the cardiovascular system. Tools and techniques used to manipulate and measure mechanical forces at the molecular, cellular, tissue, and organ levels, and their applications in cardiovascular devices and tissue engineering.",""," Master of Engineering students only. Graduate students only.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 213","Systems Cell and Developmental Biology","4","Introduces concepts needed to understand cell and developmental biology at the systems level, i.e., how the parts (molecules) work together to create a complex output. Emphasis on using mathematical/computational modeling to expand/modify insights provided by intuition.",""," Graduate students only.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("BME 215","Linking Modeling and Experiments in Bioengineering","4","Overview of modeling based on experimental techniques in bioengineering. Construct and evaluate models of varying complexity and to relate them to experimental data."," BME 220 and BME 221"," Graduate students only.");
