INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 1","Introduction to Chemical Engineering","1","Helps new students successfully transition to UCI, build a sense of community in the department, develop networking and professional skills, and introduce a variety of industries who employ chemical engineers through a series of guest lectures.",""," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 40A","Chemical Processes and Material Balances","4","Introduction to chemical engineering and the industries where chemical engineers play vital roles. Problem-solving skills and techniques. Quantitative calculations and applications using mass and energy balances. Stoichiometric equations, multiple bypasses, and others in process industries."," MATH 2B and PHYS 7C and (CHEM 1B or CHEM H2B)"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Environmental Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 40B","Process Thermodynamics","3","Principles of thermodynamics: definitions, basic concepts, and laws"," CBE 40A and (MATH 3A or ICS 6N). CBE 40A with a grade of C- or better"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 40C","Chemical Engineering Thermodynamics","4","Elements of chemical engineering thermodynamics, including equilibrium and stability",""," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 100","Introduction to Numerical Methods in Engineering","3","An introduction to the fundamentals of numerical analysis and the computer algorithms in MATLAB for the solution of engineering problems, with emphasis on problems arising in chemical engineering thermodynamics, transport phenomena, and reaction engineering."," CBE 40C"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 105","Engineering Physical Chemistry","4","Provides an integrated view of both classical and molecular perspectives on thermodynamics, thermodynamic potentials, entropy, and the second law. Students learn how to use statistical mechanics to create a bridge between the quantum mechanical world and the familiar macroscopic one."," CHEM 1C and CBE 40C and (PHYS 7D or PHYS 7E)"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 110","Reaction Kinetics and Reactor Design","4","Introduction to quantitative analysis of chemical reactions and chemical reactor design. Reactor operations including batch, continuous stirred tank, and tubular reactor. Homogeneous and heterogeneous reactions."," CHEM 1C and MATH 3D and CBE 40B and CBE 40C and CBE 100. CBE 40B with a grade of C- or better. CBE 40C with a grade of C- or better"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Materials Science and Engineering majors have second consideration for enrollment. ");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 120A","Momentum Transfer","4","Fluid statics, surface tension, Newton's law of viscosity, non-Newtonian and complex flows, momentum equations, laminar and turbulent flow, velocity profiles, flow in pipes and around objects, piping systems design, pumps and mixing, and other applications to chemical and related industries."," CBE 40C and MATH 3D. CBE 40C with a grade of C- or better"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 120B","Heat Transfer","3","Principles of conduction, radiation, and convection of heat"," CBE 120A. CBE 120A with a grade of C- or better"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Materials Science and Engineering majors have second consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 120C","Mass Transfer","3","Molecular and continuum approaches to diffusion and convection in multi-component mixtures"," CBE 120B and CBE 100"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Materials Science and Engineering majors have second consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 130","Separation Processes","4","Application of equilibria and mass and energy balances for design of separation processes. Use of equilibrium laws for design of distillation, absorption, stripping, and extraction equipment. Design of multicomponent separators."," CBE 40B and CBE 40C. CBE 40B with a grade of C- or better. CBE 40C with a grade of C- or better"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Materials Science and Engineering majors have second consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 140A","Chemical Engineering Laboratory I","4","Experimental study of thermodynamics, fluid mechanics, and heat and mass transfer. Operation and evaluation of process equipment, data analysis.  Materials fee."," CBE 110 and CBE 120C"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 140B","Chemical Engineering Laboratory II","4","Continuation of the CBE 140A covering mass transfer operations such as distillation, absorption, extraction, etc. Rate and equilibria studies in simple chemical systems with and without reaction. Study of chemical process. Materials fee."," CBE 130 and CBE 145 and CBE 140A"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("CBE 145","Chemical Process Control","4","Dynamic responses and control of chemical process equipment, dynamic modeling of chemical processes, linear system analysis, analyses and design of feedback loops and advanced control systems."," CBE 110 and CBE 120B and CBE 120C"," Chemical Engineering Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
