INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("SOCIOL 135","Social Psychology of Networks","4","Review of network methods used in small group and organizational research. Discussion of social psychological literature relevant to the network of study of cognitive social structure, exchange/communication, identity negotiation, and social control. Case study of network datasets exemplifies research issues.",""," Sociology Majors have first consideration for enrollment. Psychology Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("SOCIOL 136","Religious Traditions of Asian Americans","4","Studies the religious traditions of Asian Americans, focusing on the transplantation of religious institutions, establishment of sacred spaces, celebration of religious holidays, socialization of children, as well as birth, marriage, gender relations, death, family.","","");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("SOCIOL 138","Business Decisions","4","Surveys normative and descriptive models of decision-making behavior, with an emphasis on organizational and policy contexts. Topics include rational choice theory, biases and heuristics, framing effects, and overconfidence. Management fads, panics, and herd behavior are also discussed."," (ANTHRO 10A and ANTHRO 10B and ANTHRO 10C) or (SOCIOL 10A and SOCIOL 10B and SOCIOL 10C) or (SOC SCI 10A and SOC SCI 10B and SOC SCI 10C) or (MATH 2A and MATH 2B and (STATS 7 or MGMT 7)) or (STATS 120A and STATS 120B and STATS 120C) or (ECON 15A and ECON 15B)"," Sociology Majors have first consideration for enrollment.");
