INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("UNI STU 10","Introduction to Civic and Community Engagement and Community Research","4","Provides a foundation for understanding the role of public scholarship, civic engagement, and social action, and the relationship between service learning and engaged citizenship. Introduces key theoretical and research methodologies on the traditions and innovations of civic and community engagement.","","");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("UNI STU 13C","Introduction to Global Sustainability III","4","Introduces Earth as a system and living planet. Examines physical and biological resources as well as energy, water, climate, and ecosystems. Introduces and applies analytic lens of environmental, social, and economic sustainability to examine human impacts and resource use."," UNI STU 13B","");
