INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("WRITING 39A","Introduction to Writing and Rhetoric","4","Introduction to the principles of rhetoric through readings and writing assignments across a range of genres, including fiction, non-fiction, journalism and academic essays. Rigorous instruction in composition and style, including organization, paragraph development, sentence-level mechanics. Letter Grade with P/NP Option."," Placement via the UC Analytical Writing Placement Examination is required.","");
INSERT INTO courses VALUES ("WRITING 39AP","Introduction to Writing and Rhetoric with Lab","6","Introduces the principles of rhetoric through readings and writing assignments across a range of genres. Rigorous instruction in composition and style. Designed for students seeking additional English language support. Letter Grade with P/NP Option."," Students must have taken the UC Analytical Writing Placement Examination and the Academic English Placement Test.","");
